on, Sussex, England","Ashington Manor, Chilton, England":"Chilton, Oxfordshire, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Ashington","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of Family Names in Britain and Ireland © University of the West of England 2016","meanings":["English: (i) locative name from any of various places called  <i>Ashington</i> (especially Lincs, Sussex), or Ashingdon (Essex). (ii) possibly a variant of   Ashenden   in Kent contexts; note Robt.  <i>Ashinden</i>, 1730 in   IGI   (Deal, Kent)."],"variants":[{"name":"IGI","meanings":["1  Norman, English: probably a clipped form of   Dawnay  . Compare Bridgett Dawney, 1627, George Dawne, 1629, in   IGI   (Langar, Notts).  See also  Laney   and   Dando  . Some of the following early bearers could alternatively belong with (2) through family migration.","2  English: relationship name from Middle English  <i>Dawen</i>, a variant of   Dawes   with the weak declension genitival suffix  <i>-(e)n</i> (Old English  <i>-an</i>) instead of the standard Middle English  <i>-es</i>. The usage is mainly restricted to West Midlands dialects of Middle English."]},{"name":"Ashenden","meanings":["English: locative name from Ashenden in Tenterden (Kent), which is recorded as  <i>Esserinden'</i> in 1278."]}]},{"name":"John","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["New Testament: ‘God is gracious’.  See  <b>John</b> ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When John Ashington was born about 1150, in Bramber, Sussex, England, United Kingdom, his father, Sir. Robert Ashington Baron, was 32 and his mother, Mrs. Robert Ashington, was 28. He married Mrs. John de Ashington about 1174, in Ashington with Buncton, Sussex, England. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. He died in 1230, in his hometown, at the age of 81."},"et":{"Abt 1150–1230":"umbes 1150–1230","1150–1230":"1150–1230","1154–Female":"1154–Surnud","1153–Female":"1153–Surnud","1171